[2026-07-11] RESEARCH: Legacy semantics verified against authoritative sources
    (cited in audit_report.md §6):
      * IBM Enterprise COBOL 6.4 ROUNDED phrase — bare ROUNDED increments the LSD
        when the excess digit >= 5 => NEAREST-AWAY-FROM-ZERO (round half up in
        magnitude, sign-aware). Confirms Gap-3 mitigation. NOT banker's rounding.
      * IBM intermediate precision — fixed-point intermediates cap at 30 digits
        (compat) / 31 (extended). Model uses 38; residual risk logged as Gap-6.
      * IBM APAR PH64936 — COBOL arithmetic rounding/truncation is
        compiler-version-dependent. Reinforces the mandatory live-baseline gate.
      * COMP-3 layout confirmed: BCD, 2 digits/byte, sign nibble C/F=+, D=-,
        decimal-exact. Confirms Gap-1 (use Decimal, never float).

[2026-07-11] DECISION: Money type = rust_decimal::Decimal. Rationale: COMP-3 is
    decimal-exact; f64 would inject base-2 error at the cent level. Trade-off:
    Decimal is slower than f64 — irrelevant for a batch posting job, mandatory
    for correctness. MANDATORY CONSTRAINT honored: zero f32/f64 in the money path.

[2026-07-11] DECISION: Rounding = MidpointAwayFromZero for ROUNDED, ToZero for
    the default (truncating) COMPUTE. Discriminators: half_cent_positive
    (0.005->0.01), half_cent_up_from_even (0.025->0.03, banker's would give 0.02),
    half_cent_negative (-0.005->-0.01). A banker's-rounding port would fail these.

[2026-07-11] DECISION: Single rounding event at field store; intermediate carried
    at full Decimal precision (Gap-4). Note: rust_decimal has 28 significant
    digits vs the model's 38 — empirically the 2-dp result matched on all 75 rows,
    so the difference does not bite this dataset. Re-check if inputs widen.

[2026-07-11] DECISION: Size-error handling diverges from legacy DELIBERATELY.
    Legacy has no ON SIZE ERROR => silent high-order truncation. Port returns
    AccrualError::SizeError instead (Gap-5). REQUIRES business sign-off before
    production: it converts a silent-wrong into a loud-stop. Sandbox inputs are
    bounded (|principal| <= 900,000,000.00, and a generation-time assertion
    guarantees no stored field overflows) so the equivalence set never exercises
    this branch; it is proven separately in the unit test
    size_error_on_overflow_instead_of_silent_truncation.

