# UNIT 2 — AMORTSCH (loan amortization schedule)
# ============================================================================

[2026-07-11] SANDBOX: Added tests/sandbox/gen_amort_baseline.py (Python decimal,
    no float), encoding cobol/SEMANTICS_AMORT.md. Emits amort_scenarios.csv
    (7 documented scenarios) and amort_baseline.csv (per-period rows) + SHA-256
    = ca387201019ec0e59e7b1d149e45d162b1748ff74375aee128f9496024606eb2.
    Model-derived (no cobc); same production gate as INTACCR applies.

[2026-07-11] DECISION: Scheduled payment is an INPUT, not derived from the
    annuity formula P*i/(1-(1+i)^-n). Rationale: COBOL's ** operator evaluates
    with FLOATING-POINT intermediates even inside a fixed-point COMPUTE, which
    would import float into the money path and violate the mandate. Deriving the
    payment is deferred to a separate unit with its own audit of that float
    dependency (audit_report.md, AMORTSCH "Deliberate scope choice").

[2026-07-11] DECISION: Reuse INTACCR's store_money_rounded / check_size
    (exposed pub(crate)). One rounding event per period on the current balance;
    principal split exact; final-payment reconciliation on `period == N OR
    princ >= balance` -> princ := balance. The >= boundary and last-period test
    are load-bearing (Gap-B). SizeError instead of legacy silent truncation
    under runaway negative amortization (Gap-D), bounded out of the equivalence
    set and proven separately.

[2026-07-11] TDM RED: Wrote tests/amort_equivalence.rs first, against a stub
    amort::amortize returning an empty Vec. cargo test --test amort_equivalence
    FAILED on row-count mismatch (0 vs baseline). Red recorded.

[2026-07-11] TDM GREEN: Implemented src/amort.rs. Full crate suite PASSED:
    13 unit (8 INTACCR + 5 AMORTSCH) + amort equivalence (per-period parity,
    row counts incl. early-payoff & neg-am) + INTACCR equivalence + no-float
    guard + 2 doctests. Ending balance closes to exactly 0.00 on every
    completed schedule.

[2026-07-11] CORRECTION: The INTACCR audit_report claimed enforcement "by test
