# ============================================================================
# UNIT 3 — PAYCALC (annuity payment)
# ============================================================================

[2026-07-11] RESEARCH: COBOL exponentiation semantics verified (cited in
    SEMANTICS_PAY.md): integer power => "a succession of multiplications" in
    FIXED-POINT; fractional/negative exponent => whole expression promoted to
    LONG FLOATING POINT. This is the decisive fact for the unit.

[2026-07-11] DECISION (Gap-E): Migrate the annuity payment using the
    positive-integer form P*i*f/(f-1), f=(1+i)^n, NOT the textbook
    P*i/(1-(1+i)^-n). The negative-exponent form would evaluate in IEEE-754
    double (importing float into the money path, violating the mandate); the
    integer-power form stays fixed-point decimal and is algebraically identical.
    A real migration decision, documented — not a mechanical transliteration.

[2026-07-11] DECISION (Gap-F): Stage WS-FACTOR at a fixed 9 dp (single rounding
    event) so the repeated-multiply chain's result is insensitive to the
    compiler-specific intermediate cap (IBM 30/31 vs rust_decimal 28 sig digits).
    Bounds n<=120, i<=0.05 keep f<=~372, well inside both. Empirically the
    28-digit and 38-digit models produce identical 9-dp factors on all scenarios.

[2026-07-11] DECISION (Gap-G): Zero-rate special case = straight-line
    principal/num_periods (matches legacy IF WS-RATE = ZERO; avoids f-1=0
    divide). num_periods=0 (outside the 9(3) >=1 domain) => SizeError, not a
    divide-by-zero.

[2026-07-11] AUDIT EVIDENCE: gen_pay_baseline.py computes the payment BOTH
    decimal-native and legacy-float (IEEE-754), asserting equality at the cent
    for all 8 scenarios. Proves the float->decimal swap does not change the
    customer's payment. Float path lives only in the oracle; the shipped port is
    decimal-only (no_float_guard now covers src/paycalc.rs).

[2026-07-11] TDM RED: Wrote tests/pay_equivalence.rs first, against a stub
    paycalc::payment returning zeros. FAILED (factor got 0, want 1.283361235).

[2026-07-11] TDM GREEN: Implemented src/paycalc.rs. Full crate suite PASSED:
    18 unit (8 INTACCR + 5 AMORTSCH + 5 PAYCALC) + 3 equivalence proofs +
    no-float guard + 3 doctests. Composition proof: PAYCALC's payment amortizes
    to exactly 0.00 in AMORTSCH.

[2026-07-11] STATUS: Phase 1 & 2 COMPLETE for PAYCALC against the model
