# ============================================================================
# UNIT 6 — CURRCVT (euro conversion by triangulation, EC 1103/97)
# ============================================================================

[2026-07-11] RESEARCH: EC Regulation 1103/97 verified (cited in SEMANTICS_CURR.md):
    rates = 1 euro in national currency at SIX SIGNIFICANT FIGURES, never
    rounded/truncated when converting; national<->national MUST triangulate via
    the euro; the intermediate euro is rounded to NOT LESS THAN 3 decimals; a
    direct cross-rate is lawful only if it equals the triangulated result.

[2026-07-11] DECISION (Gap-P..S): Implement lawful triangulation: euro =
    ROUND(amount/rate_from, 3); result = ROUND(euro*rate_to, minor(to)); both
    NEAREST-AWAY-FROM-ZERO. Record the WRONG direct cross-rate as audit evidence
    (2/10 scenarios diverge by a minor unit, e.g. 100 DEM->FRF: 335.38 lawful vs
    335.39 direct). Variable target minor unit (ITL/ESP = 0 dp). Unknown currency
    => AccrualError::UnknownCurrency (new variant). Intermediate-euro precision
    (3 dp) is a GATE item (Gap-Q), like INTACCR Gap-6.

[2026-07-11] TDM RED: Wrote tests/curr_equivalence.rs first, against a stub
    returning zeros. FAILED (dem_to_frf result 0 vs 335.38; unknown-currency
    test also red).

[2026-07-11] TDM GREEN: Implemented src/currcvt.rs. Full crate suite PASSED:
    36 unit + 6 equivalence proofs + no-float guard (now covering src/currcvt.rs)
    + doctests. finaudit: 6 units / 206 rows / 25 gaps / VERDICT PASS.

[2026-07-11] STATUS: Phase 1 & 2 COMPLETE for CURRCVT against the model baseline.
    BLOCKING before production: regenerate curr_baseline.csv from a live target
