[2026-07-12] DECISION: Widen the scenario sets with bounds, negative amounts and
    rounding-limit cases (the three classes most likely to hide a migration
    defect), extending each unit's generator scenarios() list. Added:
    - INTACCR (75->79): double-negative principal&rate, near-max principal at a
      high rate (new_balance just under the PIC ceiling), negative half-cent tie,
      tiny negative principal (interest underflows to zero).
    - AMORTSCH (94->105 rows): two-period clean payoff, near-max principal across
      3 periods, per-period interest rounding tie.
    - PAYCALC (8->12): max rate & max periods together, low rate over 120 periods,
      large principal at 5 yr, zero-rate single period. The decimal==float
      cross-check held for all 12 rows (no arithmetic-swap divergence).
    - DAYCOUNT (10->15): 31-Dec->31-Jan across a year, leap 29-Feb->31-Mar, a
      3-year (1080-day) span, zero rate, negative principal (signed interest).
    - BRKTCALC (9->14): exact 85k and 165k boundaries, one cent either side of a
      boundary, a rounding tie one cent into bracket 1.
    - CURRCVT (10->14): zero amount, negative amount (sign through triangulation),
      IEP->ITL (rate<1 source into a 0-dp target), large DEM->ITL whole-lira.

